<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>FTC Starter Hub</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />

  <!-- Google Font -->
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

  <!-- Styles -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/main.css?v=13">
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <div class="creator-badge">Created By FTC 25690</div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-card">
        <h1>FTC Starter Hub</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">
          A centralized hub for FTC rookie teams, students looking to join a team,
          or those interested in starting one.
        </p>

        <div class="cta-buttons">
          <a href="/start-team" class="btn btn-primary">Start a Team</a>
          <a href="/join-team" class="btn btn-secondary">Join a Team</a>
          <a href="/resources" class="btn btn-tertiary">Resources</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="find-teams">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Find and Join FTC Teams Near You</h2>
        <p>
          Use our searchable team directory to discover active FTC teams in your area. Filter by
          location, sponsor type (school, club, community), and activity level. Each team profile
          includes contact details, meeting days, and roles that are currently open.
        </p>

        <ul class="features">
          <li><strong>Search Nearby:</strong> Locate teams by city, ZIP, or distance radius.</li>
          <li><strong>Filter & Compare:</strong> Narrow results by sponsor type, focus area, and roster size.</li>
          <li><strong>Direct Contact:</strong> Message team contacts or submit a join request using built-in forms.</li>
          <li><strong>Guidance & Safety:</strong> Steps for joining a team, sponsor expectations, and recommended resources for new members.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="cta-inline">
          <a href="/teams-nearby" class="btn btn-primary">Search Teams Nearby</a>
          <a href="/join-team" class="btn btn-secondary">I Want to Join</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="how-it-works">
      <div class="container">
        <h3>How It Works</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Search:</strong> Enter your location or browse featured teams.</li>
          <li><strong>Review:</strong> Open team profiles to see meetings, photos, and mentor info.</li>
          <li><strong>Contact:</strong> Reach out using the provided contact or use the join form.</li>
          <li><strong>Join:</strong> Attend a meeting and follow sponsor requirements to become a member.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-site">
      <div class="container">
        <h3>About This Site</h3>
        <p>
          FTC Starter Hub is a lightweight community resource built to help students discover and connect with
          FIRST Tech Challenge teams, find sponsor organizations, and access curated resources and step-by-step
          guidance for starting or joining a team. We aggregate team profiles, guides, and useful links so aspiring
          builders and mentors can get started quickly.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <div class="container">
        <p><strong>Built by Evergreen Tech-a-Trons</strong> — a student engineering team focused on accessibility
           and outreach for FIRST programs. To contribute, report an issue, or request a feature, please visit
           the contact page or reach out to the Evergreen Tech-a-Trons via the site.</p>
        <p class="small">© Evergreen Tech-a-Trons — All rights reserved.</p>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </main>

  <script src="/assets/js/main.js?v=8"></script>
</body>
</html>
